<font color=red>
Magi of the <b>46th</b> re-ding</font>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvallaran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vallaran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/13/01 5:41:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=715.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Vox and Naggy</span><hr size=1> In addition to what everyone else has said about resistances, the class/level you are makes a big difference.  A level 49 wizard going against naggy is many times more preferable to a level 48 wizard against naggy because the level 48 wizard has to go way back in his spell book for his last ice based spell that does about one quarter the damage of ice comet.  Against Vox this problem isn't as great for wizards in particular.  Doees that mean that the level 48 wizard can't do naggy?  Not at all.  But having ice comet is a BIG plus you give towards making that raid successful.  I just know of many naggy raids that have failed due to lack of wizard ice comet firepower.<br>
<br>
Vallaran Mistwalker<br>
Fellowship of Luclin<br>
<br>
