Magi of the <b>47th</b> re-ding</font>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucuchulainekynthelig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuchulaine Kynthelig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 326<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/01 11:33:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=715.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Vox and Naggy</span><hr size=1> 50 FR/CR for Naggy/Vox is too low, by a long shot.<br>
<br>
100 is pushing it, especially at level 45. Your level has a direct effect on how well you resist the dragon roar, as much or more than your magic resistance. Because of this, the lower level you are, the more magis resistance you need in order to do anything other than cause lag. <br>
<br>
I have never done Naggy, but i have done Vox at 50 and 52. I have resisted the fear everytime but maybe twice with an unbuffed MR of around 70. Even with an unbuffed CR of 123 or so, I was having to heal myself about every third spell (nuke, nuke, heal, nuke, nuke, heal). <br>
<br>
The more resistance, the better. Whenever you think you have enough, get more. Sacrifice AC, sacrifice int/wis (whatever you use for mana), sacrifice +mana, sacrifice +hitpoints. At level 45, you should have an MR of at least 100 unbuffed to avoid spending the entire time running in fear. Besides that, get as much FR/CR as possible, sacrificing everything to get it.<br>
<br>
Once you get to 50+, the magic resist isn't as critical. As I said with about 70, I resisted pretty much every time. Either way, accept that you are going to die. <br>
