</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unekoj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nekoj</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/19/01 6:31:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=715.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on Vox and Naggy</span><hr size=1> Speaking as a wizard that has played for over two years, and been on countless Naggy raids.<br>
<br>
Level 45 is too low for a wizard to do any good. If I was a naggy raid leader the only players I would 'allow' at level 45 would be bards, back up clerics, any melee with 100/100 resist, and any player not expected to get close.<br>
<br>
I been in groups where all our healers were feared the entire night, that group got wiped out. Naggy is level 55 and will resist anything a level 45 will throw at it. The off chance a nuke lands it is not worth another person generating lag for that person to land a partial nuke doing 100 damage. Since Naggy is considured a 'giant' creature you will need to be as close to him as possible for a minimized chance to nuke. At level 45 with resist under 100 unbuffed you will die as a wizard with only 600-1000 HPs in the first AoE damage spell Naggy spews out.<br>
<br>
Really it all depends on what class a player is. Some classes are effective at 45, some are not. Wizards will not be able to do anything until level 49.<br>
<br>
